interface.name: gnome-inform7
interface.summary: GNOME port of the Inform 7 IDE
interface.description: GNOME Inform 7 is a GNOME port of the Inform 7 integrated development environment for Inform 7. Inform 7 is a "natural" programming language for writing interactive fiction (also known as text adventures.)

interface.name: groundhog
interface.description:
The purpose of this game is to put balls in pockets of the same color by manipulating a maze of tubes.
Homepage: http://home-2.consunet.nl/~cb007736/groundhog.html

interface.name: libcurl3-gnutls
interface.description:
libcurl is designed to be a solid, usable, reliable and portable multi-protocol file transfer library.
SSL support is provided by GnuTLS. To enable LDAP support package libldap2-dev is required.
This is the shared version of libcurl.
Homepage: http://curl.haxx.se

interface.name: libmng1
interface.description: The libmng library supports decoding, displaying, encoding, and various other manipulations of the Multiple-image Network Graphics (MNG) format image files. It uses the zlib compression library, and optionally the JPEG library by the Independent JPEG Group (IJG) and/or lcms (little cms), a color-management library by Marti Maria Saguar.

interface.name: libsdl-image1.2
interface.summary: image loading library for Simple DirectMedia Layer 1.2
interface.description: This is a simple library to load images of various formats as SDL surfaces. This library currently supports BMP, PPM, PCX, GIF, JPEG, PNG, TIFF, and XPM formats.

interface.name: libsdl-mixer1.2
interface.summary: mixer library for Simple DirectMedia Layer 1.2
interface.description:
SDL Mixer is a sample multi-channel audio mixer library. It supports 4 channels of 16 bit stereo audio, plus a single channel of music, mixed by the popular MikMod MOD, Timidity MIDI, and SMPEG MP3 libraries.
URL: http://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_mixer/

interface.name: libtasn1-3
interface.description:
Manage ASN1 (Abstract Syntax Notation One) structures. The main features of this library are: * on-line ASN1 structure management that doesn't require any C code file generation. * off-line ASN1 structure management with C code file generation containing an array. * DER (Distinguish Encoding Rules) encoding * no limits for INTEGER and ENUMERATED values
This package contains runtime libraries.

interface.name: libvorbis0a
interface.summary: The Vorbis General Audio Compression Codec
interface.description:
Ogg Vorbis is a fully open, non-proprietary, patent-and-royalty-free, general-purpose compressed audio format for audio and music at fixed and variable bitrates from 16 to 128 kbps/channel.
The Vorbis library is the primary Ogg Vorbis library.

interface.name: libvorbisfile3
interface.summary: The Vorbis General Audio Compression Codec
interface.description:
Ogg Vorbis is a fully open, non-proprietary, patent-and-royalty-free, general-purpose compressed audio format for audio and music at fixed and variable bitrates from 16 to 128 kbps/channel.
The Vorbisfile library provides a convenient high-level API for decoding and basic manipulation of all Vorbis I audio streams.
